The paper deals with resource allocation in a cellular network, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The focus on energy efficiency and green communication aligns with the systems and control (SY) category. The use of matching models and geometric programming suggests a connection to mathematical modeling (MM) and game theory (GT).
